rComments: Great professor, attend his classes. You will learn a lot. Exams are long Assignments are long The course covers a lot of content, very important to stay up to date.
I paid 100% efforts into this class and I could barely pass the course. I heard now that he would be teaching second-year accounting. Well, prepare to get your GPA crushed accounting people.

Not hard course, read book and slides and memorize! Mix of memorization, application, and MC exams. Do not need to go to class as he reads through slides, but there is participations marks. Exams are fair if you study, MC from book or slides. short answers like ER diagrams, and matrix worth quite a bit. Participation focuses on homework too!

It isn't too hard to get a good grade in this class, but every lecture he just rushed through 3 hours worth of slides and was never very clear on any important points. 10% of the grade was participation, but half the time when you would answer a question, his response was a flat out 'no'. The test/project/grading criteria was not always clear.
One month into this semester and it is evident this prof is awful. Does not explain concepts well, tough to understand. Make sure you take this class with Prof. Bozec.
